    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of the research and the plan I've written:\n\n---\n\n## What I Found\n\nI read the complete source of the Nostr and IRC plugins, the plugin SDK type contracts, all public entrypoints, and the naming invariant tests. Key findings:\n\n**Architecture pattern** (16 files per plugin):\n- Root: `openclaw.plugin.json`, `package.json`, `index.ts`, `api.ts`, `runtime-api.ts`, `setup-entry.ts`\n- `src/`: `channel.ts`, `types.ts`, `runtime.ts`, `config-schema.ts`, `normalize.ts`, `send.ts`, `monitor.ts`, `inbound.ts`, `probe.ts`, `setup-surface.ts`\n\n**Important discovery about group dispatch**: There is no `dispatchInboundGroupWithRuntime` in the public SDK. IRC's `dispatchInboundReplyWithBase` — which handles both DMs and group messages — is only accessible via `openclaw/plugin-sdk/irc` or `openclaw/plugin-sdk/nextcloud-talk` (channel-specific bundles). So PulseBoard's board inbound dispatch must use the `PluginRuntime` channel API building blocks directly: `core.channel.routing.resolveAgentRoute` → `core.channel.reply.finalizeInboundContext` → `core.channel.session.recordInboundSession` → `core.channel.reply.dispatchReplyWithBufferedBlockDispatcher`.\n\n**No per-package tsconfig.json** needed — none of the existing extension packages have one.\n\n## The Plan\n\n- **16 new files** all in `extensions/pulseboard/`\n- Single-account model (like Nostr), REST polling transport (fictional), `direct` + `group` chat types, 4000-char chunk limit\n- Target format: `dm:<userId>` / `@<userId>` for DMs, `board:<name>` / `#<name>` for boards\n- Naming invariants satisfied: `@openclaw/pulseboard`, `openclaw.channel.id = \"pulseboard\"`, `npmSpec = \"@openclaw/pulseboard\"`\n- All SDK imports from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/*` public subpaths only — no cross-extension or core imports",
